This is the day when such evils must come to an end. I have been warned that to take such a stand would cost me millions of dollars. But I have said it once and I will say it again. The real enemy of my people is here. I will not disgrace my religion, my people or myself by becoming a tool to enslave those who are fighting for their own justice, freedom and equality. If I thought the war was going to bring freedom and equality to 22 million of my people they wouldn't have to draft me, I'd join tomorrow. I have nothing to lose by standing up for my beliefs. status_message: If you're surprised by these findings, you haven't been paying attention.

Are you ready for Elizabeth Warren to run for president? Well then, Senator Warren needs to hear your personal story (yes, you!) about why it's so important that she fight for all of us as a presidential candidate.

act.tv and Ready For Warren teamed up to start a #DearElizabethWarren video campaign a few weeks ago and the results have been exciting to say the least. Dozens of people have already made powerful videos appealing directly to Elizabeth Warren explaining why they need her to run, all of which you can watch at act.tv/dearliz.

Anyone can make a video on their cell phone or webcam for this campaign, simply by looking into the camera and saying "Dear Elizabeth Warren, I need you to run because...". But that's not nearly as fun as getting together for a Dear Liz video party! 

Come join us at the 3 Knights Media studio where we'll provide drinks and snacks, answer any questions, provide plenty of inspiration, set up the equipment and make sure the videos get up online properly.

This is a fun, easy way to add your voice to the draft Warren movement in a way that can really make an impact. After all, as Warren recounts in her book, it took a personal encounter with a woman pleading with her to run for senate that ultimately persuaded her. And today, through the power of digital video and social media, all of us can bring our case right to Senator Warren herself. 

So think about what you'd tell Elizabeth Warren to persuade her to run, and hope to see you this Thursday!

p.s. Interested in hosting your own Dear Liz video party? Sign up here: http://acttv.nationbuilder.com/be_a_host

#DearElizabethWarren,

"The problems that Americans are facing, Senator, cry out for a leader who is willing to fight for us. And Senator, you are that person. Please run in 2016, we cannot wait any longer."

College student Anthony Kurdilla needs Elizabeth Warren to run, not just because she champions a fix for the student loan debt crippling millions of young Americans, but because he understands the risks we all face without a leader like Sen. Warren.
